d><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Goshan's Topic of the Day - Dictate</span><hr size=1> Dictate is the single most powerful spell you can get as an enchanter. You get 48seconds of a mobs uber damage to add o your raids total damage output. <br>
<br>
The Facts:<br>
- fixed duration 48second charm. Once charmed, you have 48 seconds to utilize your beast of burden. <br>
- highly unresistable. It resists about on the level of lifetaps so it is resistable. You just have to learn your mobs and when it will work and when it wont. Coldain Dwarves in Thurg B will resist it almost everytime <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
- Level cap is 58. <br>
<br>
There are varied uses for this spell depending on the tactic to be used of which there are three that I know of. They are all similar but the differences are what happens when charm breaks.<br>
<br>
First, Always give your hasted mob 2 fine steel class weapons. Mobs dont dual wield by default so to get their ultimate damage output, give them couple weapons with low delays. Dont give them rusty weapons. Then put your mob on the primary target and haste him. <br>
Note: Make sure you set a timer for 48seconds and hit it the second that Dictate is placed upon a mob. Timing is extremely important with this spell. <br>
<br>
1st Tactic: Use when one or two enchanters are on a raid and you want a little extra ooomph to your damage output.<br>
<br>
This tactic is the easiest. When your charm duration is nearing the end, dispel the mob to strip his haste and rapture him. If the mob is unmezzable, it is still your job to control the mob. Take him away from the other raid participants and root him. I am aligned with Giants in Velious so I dont run into this problem. Any mob I charm, I can rapture for the most part.<br>
<br>
2nd Tactic: Lots of lvl 60 enchanters on a raid. <br>
<br>
This method requires some coordination to pull off. Your enchanters need to be aware of whats going on and in what order they are to charm the mob. You are basically keeping him perma charmed for the duration of the fight by lining up your enchanters and as soon as charm breaks(dont use dispel this time, just time it), another enchanters is ready to dictate the mob and continue the fight. This is a pretty effective tactic but does require very good timing.<br>
<br>
3rd tactic: 2-3 lvl 60 enchanters on a raid and mobs of different faction.<br>
<br>
This is potentially the most damaging and awesome tactic. But requires the most coordination and can have the most go wrong. First, it will only work in areas where the primary target is on a different faction then the potential charmed mobs.(There are Kromzek faction giants in Tormax's area) It will also only work if the mob being attacked is lvl 55 or greater. It also requires that you have a monk or someone invis/fd/hidden nearby so they can hit the primary target a couple of times once the battle is engaged(Just so you dont accidentally make the corpse poof. The idea works like this. If you can charm a couple of mobs near the primary target that are on different factions then the primary target, even if the mob is not charmed anymore, he will continue fighting. So what you do is charm the mob, have him attack. Wait a few seconds to let your mob get hit and gate. Guess what happens. The mobs keep fighting. Guess what else happens? The mob returned to his primary faction so any mobs in the area on his faction will join in if they are not already engaged by player chars. Let them all fight it out until the primary target or they are near death and then everyone else rushes in and attacks. This makes a mob easy.<br>
Note: This is only the enchanter role of this tactic. The rest of the tactic is up to the Raid leaders to figure out. But this should be enough info to get your imagination running. It is a lot more detailed then this but the basic mechanics I have given. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
These are all very limitied situation tactics. But when you are dealing with 200k hp mobs,they will make a difference in the end. Also realize that Boltrons can be potentially more damaging to use. If you have a lvl 53 and below mob fighting for an entire fight vs having a lvl 58 mob fight for 48 seconds, its probably better to use Boltrons. We did a test on Dain once where we had three charmed mobs of lvl 53 or less on Dain and noone else. The mobs got Dain down to 75% by themselves. Those mobs also have 15k hp or so. They can tank far better then any PC so its easy to use CH or even Donals CH on them during a fight. Its a hell of a sight to see a mob with that many hit points get complete healed.<br>
<br>
<br>
I cant stress enough how much use it is to have this spell loaded during a raid. You never know when you are gonna get a 3 pull of unmezzable mobs. Its nice to have Dictate save the day or at least help in the matter. <br>
